spanGrp.span: He walked in circles and then went to sleep.
Í jẽk wöshkriwã' shkri shkri kepa í jẽk mã'wã köpö
woke another one up with his foot, so he hid from him.
E-gla shkiwã-ka-ite klö wa Í jẽk blá-wã í yiga
Another one came and gave him something.
He got angry; another one stayed [with him].
He got very angry because the other one took something away form him.
je ulunã'-wã tã'ĩ E-gla wã jirö mẽnẽtse í yiga
Next four more people came in;
one of them left and there remained three.
E-gla mẽnẽu í yiga í jatanã'-tana mãñã-l
On the other side there were many wating for him.
Jamĩ kenẽga tã'ĩ siga-wa tsõ í kiksö
one of them came and gave him something;
he saw it, covered it and left it;
he opened the other one, saw it and threw it in his face;
e-gla köyája-wã-ite sũã'-ite-ra je kagá-ite í wö inga
he opened the other one and threw it in the air but it fell on his own head.’
E-gla köyája-wã-ite juã'u-mĩ-ite siwã' inga Je dẽu-te í wagi bö tiá-nẽ
